title: For Sale:  Baikal IZH-46M (SOLD)
postcontent:
The Baikal IZH-46M is a competition-grade, single-shot pneumatic air gun, with a hammer-forged, rifled barrel. The gun is charged with a single stroke of an underlever cocking arm.

Unlike guns intended only for plinking, several features of competition guns such as the IZH-46M mark it as designed for high-precision shooting. For instance, the IZH-46M's rear sight can be adjusted for windage/elevation, and the trigger is adjustable for position, travel, and pull. The gun can also be dry-fired without charging. The ergonomic grip features an adjustable handrest.

The Baikal IZH-46M is the current production run of the original Baikal IZH-46. The only visible and mechanical difference is the IZH-46M is built with a slightly longer (0.5" or 12 mm +/-) air compression cylinder. As all other components except chamber length and piston stroke are the same, visually the original IZH-46 barrel appears to extend further beyond the air compression cylinder than the current IZH-46M. The extra length of the air compression cylinder allows the 46M to have a 60 ft/s (18 m/s) increase in muzzle velocity over the original 46. The IZH-46M has a muzzle velocity of approximately 470 ft/s (140 m/s).[1] In either original IZH46 or current IZH46M form, the pistol is a very consistent shooting precision 10 m airgun.

Though more expensive than many commonly available airguns, the IZH-46M is inexpensive in comparison to many similarly featured competition guns.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 92fs SCAM ALERT!!! Please read!!! *Updated*
postcontent:
I wanted everyone to see this who frequents this site as I find it quite disturbing. Below is my original post...

Just got this 92fs. Works great but last time I used one was in the Army. As a civilian it's just too big to carry and conceal. Looking for Glock 19 or 26 to trade or cash. FTF to TN resident with valid ID/Carry permit.

Then I found this email this morning...

Message from REDACTED, hit 'reply' to reply to the original sender.

Message regarding post 'Beretta 92fs in box w/2 mags'

REMEMBER: Avoid scams by dealing locally and NEVER send money orders, cashiers checks, or wire money to sellers.

Just why are you trying to sell it for more than the price of a new one! Profiteering on gun sales is a direct violation of BATF regulation and a Federal Criminal Offense. You are gun dealing with out a Federal Firearms License. This ad is forwarded with formal complaint to the BATF!
This message sent from REDACTED on behalf of REDACTED. Copyright Armslist LLC 2011.

I felt like a public response was in order...

Dear REDACTED,

     Thank you for your interest in my ad. Would be nice if you have some questions about my wanting to trade my Beretta that I purchased recently for a Glock 19/26 that you simply ask. I was not aware that I was required to consult you before selling/trading on ARMSLIST to make sure the trade or sale meets your approval in advance and for that I apologize. I will be sure everyone is aware that you are sending these type of messages so they may avoid the pleasure of making your acquaintance in person. 

Thanks,
"The Profiteer"

This guy has some balls...FYI I only have 2 guns...cause I work for a living and can't afford more...I guess I should feel flattered that this retard thinks I am a "Profiteer" or "gun dealer" but that is just not the case...were it not for my tax refund I couldn't have even bought the Beretta to begin with...Looks like I am going to trade for a Glock 19 Gen 4 in Maryville later today...My wife is thrilled cause she likes my Glock 23 all but the recoil...and also because after this trade we can both quit our jobs and retire :)

If trade falls through I will repost

*** UPDATE I guess this guy is hitting several people...I have had several people inform me this is a fishing/spam type thing...so DON'T REPLY instead flag it as spam and report this idiot...one person did reply to him and it came back with the name Danny Padula on the email...hope this helps keep this GREAT website safer for all the good people to use...thanks for all the positive responses and I did trade for the Glock :) I will let this ad ride the full time hoping to warn everyone I can about this guy...

title: For Sale/Trade:  1895 Chilean 7mm Mauser
postcontent:
I have a model 1895 Chilean Mauser chambered in 7x57 Mauser.  The bore is dark with good rifling.  Metal finish is worn with some minor pitting towards the muzzle but overall decent for its age.

The gun was "sporterized" by someone who, in some places, did a very nice job.  The bolt handle was bent, the receiver was drilled and tapped for scope mounts (included, needs a couple new screws), the stock profile was thinned, and the handguard was removed.  

I fitted a replacement handguard and retaining ring, replaced the mangled rear barrel band, replaced the front barrel band, found part of a rear sight, replaced the cut-down bolt safety, and added tall scope rings (included).

Its a good shooter but its in a caliber I don't really have a use for and its just taking up space in my gun cabinet.  The wood ought to be refinished and the bolt polished, but aside from that its not a bad looking rifle.  

Send me an email, I'm open to offers or trades so just let me know what you have.
